*   [\~nedia/auto-save.nvim](https://git.sr.ht/~nedia/auto-save.nvim) - Extremely simple auto saving on `InsertLeave` & `TextChanged`. Based on Pocco81/AutoSave but lighter.

items.title: Awesome Python Data Science
items.content_text: ### Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning * [dlib (‚≠ê14k)](https://github.com/davisking/dlib) - Toolkit for making real-world machine learning and data analysis applications in C++ (Python bindings). ### Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods * [Stacking (‚≠ê224)](https://github.com/ikki407/stacking) - Simple and useful stacking library written in Python. ### Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets * [imbalanced-learn (‚≠ê7k)](https://github.com/scikit-learn-contrib/imbalanced-learn) - Module to perform under-sampling and over-sampling with various techniques. ### Deep Learning / PyTorch * [skorch (‚≠ê6.1k)](https://github.com/dnouri/skorch) - A scikit-learn compatible neural network library that wraps PyTorch. * [ChemicalX (‚≠ê745)](https://github.com/AstraZeneca/chemicalx) - A PyTorch-based deep learning library for drug pair scoring. ### Deep Learning / TensorFlow * [tfdeploy (‚≠ê354)](https://github.com/riga/tfdeploy) - Deploy TensorFlow graphs for fast evaluation and export to TensorFlow-less environments running numpy. * [Ludwig (‚≠ê12k)](https://github.com/uber/ludwig) - A toolbox that allows one to train and test deep learning models without the need to write code. * [Hyperas (‚≠ê2.2k)](https://github.com/maxpumperla/hyperas) - Keras + Hyperopt: A straightforward wrapper for a convenient hyperparameter. ### Model Explanation / Others * [dalex (‚≠ê1.4k)](https://github.com/ModelOriented/DALEX) - moDel Agnostic Language for Exploration and explanation. * [Shapley (‚≠ê220)](https://github.com/benedekrozemberczki/shapley) - A data-driven framework to quantify the value of classifiers in a machine learning ensemble. * [tensorboard-pytorch (‚≠ê8k)](https://github.com/lanpa/tensorboard-pytorch) - Tensorboard for PyTorch (and chainer, mxnet, numpy, ...). ### Optimization / Others * [sklearn-genetic-opt (‚≠ê343)](https://github.com/rodrigo-arenas/Sklearn-genetic-opt) - Hyperparameters tuning and feature selection using evolutionary algorithms. * [OR-Tools](https://developers.google.com/optimization) - An open-source software suite for optimization by Google; provides a unified programming interface to a half dozen solvers: SCIP, GLPK, GLOP, CP-SAT, CPLEX, and Gurobi. ### Experimentation / Synthetic Data * [Neptune](https://neptune.ai) - A lightweight ML experiment tracking, results visualization, and management tool. * [Sacred (‚≠ê4.3k)](https://github.com/IDSIA/sacred) - A tool to help you configure, organize, log, and reproduce experiments. ### Data Validation / Synthetic Data * [pandera (‚≠ê3.9k)](https://github.com/unionai-oss/pandera) - A lightweight, flexible, and expressive statistical data testing library. ### Evaluation / Synthetic Data * [sklearn-evaluation (‚≠ê3)](https://github.com/edublancas/sklearn-evaluation) - Model evaluation made easy: plots, tables, and markdown reports. * [AI Fairness 360 (‚≠ê2.6k)](https://github.com/IBM/AIF360) - Fairness metrics for datasets and ML models, explanations, and algorithms to mitigate bias in datasets and models. ### Quantum Computing / Synthetic Data * [cirq (‚≠ê4.6k)](https://github.com/quantumlib/Cirq) - A python framework for creating, editing, and invoking Noisy Intermediate Scale Quantum (NISQ) circuits. ### Conversion / Synthetic Data * [sklearn-porter (‚≠ê1.3k)](https://github.com/nok/sklearn-porter) - Transpile trained scikit-learn estimators to C, Java, JavaScript, and others.
items.content_html:
Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning

  • dlib (‚≠ê14k) - Toolkit for making real-world machine learning and data analysis applications in C++ (Python bindings).

Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods

  • Stacking (‚≠ê224) - Simple and useful stacking library written in Python.

Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets

  • imbalanced-learn (‚≠ê7k) - Module to perform under-sampling and over-sampling with various techniques.

Deep Learning / PyTorch

  • skorch (‚≠ê6.1k) - A scikit-learn compatible neural network library that wraps PyTorch.
  • ChemicalX (‚≠ê745) - A PyTorch-based deep learning library for drug pair scoring.

Deep Learning / TensorFlow

  • tfdeploy (‚≠ê354) - Deploy TensorFlow graphs for fast evaluation and export to TensorFlow-less environments running numpy.
  • Ludwig (‚≠ê12k) - A toolbox that allows one to train and test deep learning models without the need to write code.
  • Hyperas (‚≠ê2.2k) - Keras + Hyperopt: A straightforward wrapper for a convenient hyperparameter.

Model Explanation / Others

  • dalex (‚≠ê1.4k) - moDel Agnostic Language for Exploration and explanation.
  • Shapley (‚≠ê220) - A data-driven framework to quantify the value of classifiers in a machine learning ensemble.
  • tensorboard-pytorch (‚≠ê8k) - Tensorboard for PyTorch (and chainer, mxnet, numpy, ...).

Optimization / Others

  • sklearn-genetic-opt (‚≠ê343) - Hyperparameters tuning and feature selection using evolutionary algorithms.
  • OR-Tools - An open-source software suite for optimization by Google; provides a unified programming interface to a half dozen solvers: SCIP, GLPK, GLOP, CP-SAT, CPLEX, and Gurobi.

Experimentation / Synthetic Data

  • Neptune - A lightweight ML experiment tracking, results visualization, and management tool.
  • Sacred (‚≠ê4.3k) - A tool to help you configure, organize, log, and reproduce experiments.

Data Validation / Synthetic Data

  • pandera (‚≠ê3.9k) - A lightweight, flexible, and expressive statistical data testing library.

Evaluation / Synthetic Data

  • sklearn-evaluation (‚≠ê3) - Model evaluation made easy: plots, tables, and markdown reports.
  • AI Fairness 360 (‚≠ê2.6k) - Fairness metrics for datasets and ML models, explanations, and algorithms to mitigate bias in datasets and models.

Quantum Computing / Synthetic Data

  • cirq (‚≠ê4.6k) - A python framework for creating, editing, and invoking Noisy Intermediate Scale Quantum (NISQ) circuits.

Conversion / Synthetic Data

  • sklearn-porter (‚≠ê1.3k) - Transpile trained scikit-learn estimators to C, Java, JavaScript, and others.

items.title: Awesome Agi Cocosci
items.content_text:
### Meta-Level Considerations / Rationality

*   [Foundations of intuitive power analyses in children and adults](https://eccl.mit.edu/s/Pelz_Foundations-of-intuitive-power-analyses-in-children-and-adults.pdf) - ***Nature Human Behavior***, 2022. \[[All Versions](https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=4370839893505978405\&hl=en\&as_sdt=0,5)]. Evidences support that people have some of the foundations for 'intuitive power analyses', which help people use intuitive statistical reasoning and metacognitive strategies to estimate how much information they might need to solve different discrimination problems.
